{{Infobox organization | name = Commercial Real Estate Women (CREW) Network | logo = [[File:CREW Network Logo.jpg|centre|150px]] | vector_logo = [[File:CREW Network Logo.jpg|centre|150px]] | type = Professional association | founded_date = 1989 | founder = | first president = | location_city = Lawrence | location_country = USA | location = [[Lawrence, KS]], [[United States of America]] | area_served = U.S.A and Canada | origins = | key_people = | focus = Advancement of women in commercial real estate | method = Research initiative, Professional development sessions and Business networking | revenue = | num_members = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = To advance the success of women in commercial real estate. | homepage = [http://www.crewnetwork.org CREW Network] | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
'''Commercial Real Estate Women''' (CREW) Network is a [[professional association]] for women in the [[real estate]] profession. There are various chapters of CREW throughout the [[United States]] which create programming focused on business networking, social and educational programs and the advancement of women in [[commercial real estate]].
== About == Commercial Real Estate Women (CREW) Network works to educate women about opportunities in [[Commercial property|commercial real estate]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/bizwomen/news/profiles-strategies/2016/11/building-a-better-pipeline-in-commercial-real.html?page=all|title=Building a better pipeline in commercial real estate|last=Wylie|first=Melissa|date=|website=Biz Journals|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-12}}</ref> The organization was founded in 1989.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crewnetwork.org/about|title=About|last=|first=|date=|website=CREW Network|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-12}}</ref> CREW has over 11,000 members worldwide, and the organization has four main initiatives: Business Development, Industry Research, Leadership Development, and Career Outreach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crewnetwork.org/about|title=CREW Network - About|website=crewnetwork.org|access-date=2018-10-22}}</ref>
Various chapters of CREW exist throughout the [[United States]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-376072159.html|title=NY Commercial Real Estate Women: Creating Connections|last=|first=|date=16 July 2014|work=Real Estate Weekly|access-date=12 August 2018|subscription=yes|via=HighBeam Research}}</ref> Most chapters focus on [[Business networking|networking]], social and educational activities for members.<ref name=":0" /> By 2007, there were 61 individual chapters in various states.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=bwh&AN=27221578&site=ehost-live|title=Commercial Real Estate Women Form Local Chapter|last=|first=|date=15 October 2007|work=Enterprise/Salt Lake City|access-date=12 August 2018|subscription=yes|via=EBSCOhost}}</ref>
In 1998, CREW created a fund-raising and philanthropic program called CREW Foundation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-174372989.html|title=NYCREW builds opportunities.(New York Commercial Real Estate Women)|last=|first=|date=30 January 2008|work=Real Estate Weekly|access-date=12 August 2018|subscription=yes|via=HighBeam Research}}</ref> CREW also has a national conference.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=f5h&AN=2008315&site=ehost-live|title=Conference participants see Detroit's potential|last=Hubbard|first=Linda|date=28 June 1999|work=Crain's Detroit Business|access-date=12 August 2018|subscription=yes|via=EBSCOhost}}</ref>
