{{italic title}} {{Other uses|E24 (disambiguation){{!}}E24}} '''''E24 Næringsliv''''', formerly '''''N24''''', is a [[Norway|Norwegian]], [[online newspaper|online]] business newspaper launched on 18 April 2006.
During the first three years of operation, the newspaper was owned 60% by ''[[Aftenposten]]'' and 40% by ''[[Verdens Gang]]'' (''VG''), both fully owned by public media company [[Schibsted]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Eric Pfanner|title=While Others Struggle, Norwegian Newspaper Publisher Thrives on the Web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/19/business/media/19papers.html?pagewanted=print&_r=0|accessdate=13 January 2015|work=The New York Times|date=19 February 2007}}</ref> ''[[Verdens Gang]]'' (''VG'') owns 100% of E24 Næringsliv.
In the course of the first week of operations it became the largest business web site in Norway. In week 46, 2008, it had 575,000 [[unique users]] per week.
In 2013 ''E24 Næringsliv'' merged with monthly business magazine ''[[Dine Penger]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Annual editorial report 2014|url=http://np.netpublicator.com/np/n76968510/Annual-editorial-report-2013-LOW-OK.pdf|work=Net Publicator|accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref>
